item.title: Response (Short Doc)
item.dc:creator: bob_kiberd_95
item.content:encoded:
Response - Short Documentary
Response is a 10-minute short documentary highlighting the work of two search and rescue organisations in Ireland; Drogheda River Rescue & Recovery and Waterford Marine Search & Rescue. The documentary focuses on the people in these organisations, as well as their work in suicide prevention within their local communities. I took the role of director and lead editor in the project, as well as contributing to graphic elements of the project additional filming of footage.
WINNER OF ‘BEST 2ND YEAR GROUP PROJECT 2015’ 
Institute of Technology Blanchardstown
The ‘Second Year Group Project’ is a year-long project in the Creative Digital Media course, in which, over the course of the academic year, groups of 4 are tasked with completing a  large project, in our case, a ten-minute short documentary. These projects can be video-based, website development and design, animation, or rebranding and graphic design. Our short documentary, ‘Response’, was awarded as joint-winner along with a short animation.
[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zSHm7gv9BFk&t=3s[/embed]

item.title: Blue of the Night (Video)
item.dc:creator: bob_kiberd_95
item.content:encoded:
RTÉ Blue of the Night: Live from Kaleidoscope
This video for RTÉ's Lyric FM was the first commission I had for the 'Blue of the Night' programme. Along with my collaboration partner, Brendan Corcoran, I directed and edited this short highlight video for the Kaleidoscope live event, which ran in June 2016. This was the first piece of commercial work I was involved in, which brought forward a new challenge for me as a filmmaker, as this video came with a lot less license for abstract creativity, compared to the music video work I had previously been commissioned for. This allowed my to hone my skills in this style of production and editing. We filmed various acts that performed throughout the event and put together a short highlight video for programme's online and social media platforms.
[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=77dqyCw2wuM[/embed]

item.title: Maria Greenan (Music Video)
item.dc:creator: bob_kiberd_95
item.content:encoded:
"Maria Greenan - I Put a Spell On You"
Music Video
This was the second music video I worked on, under the title of 'Able Frame', the production team, consisting of myself and colleague, Brendan Corcoran. After consultation with the artist, Maria Greenan and her producer Ben Rawlins, we directed this abstract piece based around a live performance.After seeing our first video, 'Dramamine', both Greenan and Rawlins had asked us to incorporate a similar style, i.e. keeping the video heavy in abstract visuals using stock and archive footage.
Although we could take our experience from the first video, we wanted to use this project as an opportunity to attempt to bridge the gap between the abstract nature of our previous video, as had been requested, while making the video slightly more approachable for a broader audience as we felt this fit the target audience better for this particular project.
[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=adwL8OP6zns[/embed]

item.title: Music Artwork
item.dc:creator: bob_kiberd_95
item.content:encoded:
In working with artists' in the realm of music video production, I have also been commissioned to produce some artwork for musical releases. Here are some examples of my artwork produced for artists’ and some concept album/single artwork. I have worked with both my own imagery and existing images, given to me by my clients to produce these various artworks. I find this sort of work to be a great way to output some abstract creativity, and also produce designs that please the various clients.
<hr />

item.title: Owensie (Music Video)
item.dc:creator: bob_kiberd_95
item.content:encoded:
Owensie - 'Dramamine'  Music Video
The music video for 'Dramamine' by the Irish artist Owensie was the first music video I produced with my colleague and collaboration partner, Brendan Corcoran. We worked under the name 'Able Frame' for this project and various other projects afterward.
'Dramamine' was an experimental music video, I took the project as an opportunity to try out some new ideas and skills in order to advance my editing skills. I worked on all aspects of the project, from concept to the final cut. We used a mixture of stock images and footage and our own captured work to produce the abstract piece, which we had agreed upon with the artist.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u7WKNwHklW8

item.title: Order Point (Branding Project)
item.dc:creator: bob_kiberd_95
item.content:encoded:
Order Point is a tech start-up company, working in the hospitality point-of-sale industry. I was tasked with designing a logo and overall brand strategy for the company and product. Although the product that Order Point are selling is a modern point-of-sale device which is revolutionary in it's design, the audience the product is aimed at, i.e. upper and middle hotel management, is much more conservative. I designed this logo and brand strategy to bridge this gap between the modern and the corporate worlds that this company crosses.
Here as some examples of my design on various touch-points.
<hr />
[envira-gallery id="937"]

item.title: Photography
item.dc:creator: bob_kiberd_95
item.content:encoded:
Since joining the Creative Digital Media course In 2014, I have taken various opportunities to improve my skills and knowledge of film through photography. Although initially I had a much greater interest in post-production, my love for photography and cinematography over the past few years has grown and grown. I have worked on various small photography projects over that last number of years.
Benefit - Medlar In 2015, I did some photography work for Dublin clubnight, 'Benefit', in the Twister Pepper, formally a small underground nightclub on North Dublin's Abbey Street. Here are some examples of my event photography from Benefit's event for house producer and DJ, Medlar.
[envira-gallery id="911"]
Misc. Here are some examples of other photography work. Although I mainly work in video, I like to work with stills and photography to gain as much experience as I can, when I can. This gallery includes excerpts from a photo essay I completed on graffiti artist, 'Cresface'.
[envira-gallery id="894"]

item.title: Graphic Design/Typography
item.dc:creator: bob_kiberd_95
item.content:encoded:
Over the course of my study at the Institute of Technology Blanchardstown, I have completed various designs and graphic works. Below are some examples of posters I have designed and one short kinetic typography animation I made as part of college projects. the examples below are two of my poster designs, both made for college, as well as an animation I created using Adobe Flash CC for a ‘Multimedia Authoring’ module. I often try to use poster design to explore graphic design ideas, as I think it's a great way to put forward an idea as one single piece as oppose to larger design projects. Animation, while not being my strong suit, is a great way for me to further explore ideas and designs I have had.
[envira-gallery id="927"]

item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: bob_kiberd_95
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!
